    "created_at": "2026-05-22T06:46:26Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-05-22T06:46:26Z",
    "body": "I experience the same behaviour on Fedora with ghostty, but not with the default ptyxis. I noticed that the difference was that ghostty default cursor is a line, while ptyxis is a block. I changed the ghostty's cursor to block and the issue seems to be gone. \nSo adding \n```\ncursor-style = block\n```\nto `~/.config/ghostty/config` helped in my case.",
